simple-tooltip


Installation

$ gem install simple_tooltip

Within your Rails application
run the installer

$ rails generate simple_tooltip:install

The generator creates a SimpleTooltip model, etc


Create the simple_tooltips table in your database

$ rake db:migrate



1: Make sure you have the jQuery JavaScript library installed
   via the jquery-rails gem
   $ rails generate jquery:install

2: Check that these lines are in layouts/application.html.erb

  <%= stylesheet_link_tag :all %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag :defaults %>

3: Add this line after those two

  <%= javascript_include_tag 'simple_tooltip.js' %>

4: Create the simple_tooltips database table

   $ rake db:migrate

5: Create some tooltip entries in /simple_tooltips
   and add links to those entries in your views
   <%= simple_tooltip('tooltip title', :hover) %>
